  "description": "Byung-Chul Han (1959–) is a Korean-German philosopher whose work develops a phenomenology of late-neoliberal subjectivity — the achievement-subject, the burnout society, the transparency society, psychopolitics — extending Foucauldian analysis of power into conditions in which subjects exploit themselves under the affective grammar of freedom.",
